"t_title27","蔣萬安宣布不選北市長 姚文智：有點失望
        
            
        
    "," 2018年6月12日•星期二•戊戌年四月廿九日"," 為達最佳瀏覽效果，建議使用 Chrome、Firefox 或 Internet Explorer 10(含) 以上版本的瀏覽器。 爆  〔記者蘇芳禾／台北報導〕被視為國民黨角逐台北市長強棒的立委蔣萬安，昨天宣布不選台北市長，民進黨內評估，蔣萬安不選的結果，確實意外地拆除一顆不小的炸彈，不過鬆了一口氣的人應該是台北市長柯文哲。 黨內幹部評估，台北市選戰對其他縣市有外溢效果，這次蔣萬安不選市長，對於民進黨是否與柯文哲合作關聯性較小，基本上綠營、柯營合作，還是取決於雙方的關係。 一名市議員也認為，民進黨沒有像國民黨這麼複雜，最後就是比民調，若柯文哲民調贏，基本上合作機率就很高，民進黨很理性科學。 一名選舉操盤手則說，前陣子的一場北市綠營里長座談中，有一半挺柯文哲，一半堅持民進黨要自提人選，他希望大家能夠支持黨的決定，不然黨最後無論做什麼決定，都有一半的人不支持，這種分裂絕對會造成綠營損害，柯文哲若因此敗選，可能還會順勢選總統。民進黨現在決定台北市長是否合作，只是讓綠營內部先打一架而已，沒有好處。 已表態爭取台北市長選舉提名的民進黨立委姚文智表示，他覺得有點失望，蔣萬安若參選會是比較有趣的選舉，如果不選也算是俐落負責的表現。 姚文智指出，市長選舉最終還是市政發展方向和願景，過去選了柯文哲，三年下來覺得柯文哲並沒有準備好，市政一敗塗地。 至於傳出柯文哲向駐日代表、謝系掌門人謝長廷請益，甚至要請謝擔任競選總幹事，身為謝系大弟子的姚文智則說，「想像力太豐富」，這樣他可能要找前美國總統歐巴馬或蔡英文總統當他的總幹事。 姚說，不要這樣隨便吃別人豆腐，他也常和謝院長聯絡、交換意見，選舉酸言酸語就算了，隨便吃人豆腐不太好。 對於國民黨另一可能對手丁守中，姚文智認為，丁守中廿年來做了很多準備，但很多方向，比如說廢除機場等想法，並沒看到城市的未來。他說，丁的準備恐怕是從廿年開始發想，雖然廿年沒有進步，不過總是可以在市政的未來性方面做好的辯論。 國民黨立委蔣萬安昨宣布不參加年底台北市長選舉，已表態爭取台北市長選舉提名的民進黨立委姚文智昨回應「有一點失望」。（記者廖振輝攝） 新聞送上來！快加入自由電子報APP、LINE好友  2018年6月12日•星期二•戊戌年四月廿九日 注目新聞 1 中國卡車罷工延燒 司機高喊「打倒共產黨」！ 2 洋腸又來！夜店外帶18歲妹 網站取名「台女很容易」... 3 侯友宜妻1塊土地99個門牌 蘇貞昌：太荒唐 4 突破中國封鎖打入國際！台灣成為ICH會員 5 G7峰會氣氛有多糟？ 梅克爾PO照片說明一切！","8"
"t_title28","《TAIPEI TIMES》 Chiang Wan-an opts out of Taipei mayor election
        
            
        
    "," 2018年6月12日•星期二•戊戌年四月廿九日"," 為達最佳瀏覽效果，建議使用 Chrome、Firefox 或 Internet Explorer 10(含) 以上版本的瀏覽器。 爆  By Sean Lin / Staff reporter Chinese Nationalist Party （KMT） Legislator Chiang Wan-an （蔣萬安） yesterday said that he would not seek the KMT’s nomination for the Taipei mayoral election in November. “I never said that I would run. I will stay at the Legislative Yuan,” Chiang said. He said that he would continue as KMT caucus convener for the legislature’s Social Welfare and Environmental Hygiene Committee to check and balance administrative power. He is to focus his attention on bills that address labor rights, air pollution and food safety when scrutinizing the ruling Democratic Progressive Party （DPP）, he added. Chiang said he decided to remain a legislator after the DPP this month pushed amendments to the Labor Standards Act （勞動基準法） through the legislature, rendering his efforts to review the amendments futile and degrading relevant agencies into “rubber stamps.” Asked whether the KMT would appoint him as its Taipei mayoral candidate, forcing him to run, he said such a scenario is “out of the question.” Asked whether he would lend his support to KMT Taipei mayoral candidate hopeful Ting Shou-chung （丁守中）, a former KMT legislator, Chiang said he would back anyone who emerges as the winner in the party’s primary. He had made his position on the election clear to KMT Chairman Wu Den-yih （吳敦義）, he added. KMT caucus whip Lin Te-fu （林德福） said he respected Chiang’s decision. KMT caucus deputy secretary-general William Tseng （曾銘宗） said he had high hopes for Chiang, but respected his decision. It is unlikely that Chiang would be “drafted” by the KMT for the Taipei mayoral election, Tseng added. Separately yesterday, Ting applauded Chiang for deciding to stay in the “battlefield” at the legislature. “This is an act of shouldering responsibility that deserves recognition,” Ting said, adding that it would take party unity for the KMT to win back Taipei. KMT Culture and Communications Committee director-general Lee Ming-hsien （李明賢） said he respected Chiang’s decision, adding that it would not affect the party’s plan to nominate someone through a primary who is most likely to win the election. The nominations of all candidates for city mayor and county commissioner posts in November’s nine-in-one local elections would be based on public opinion polls, rather than surveys of only KMT members, Lee said. The nomination process for Taipei and New Taipei City mayoral candidates is expected to begin after the Lunar New year holiday next month, he said. DPP Legislator Pasuya Yao （姚文智）, who is seeking the DPP’s nomination for Taipei mayoral candidate, said he was slightly disappointed by Chiang’s announcement. It would be far more interesting if Chiang is in the race, Yao said. Chiang’s decision was both graceful and a responsible move, as it allows the KMT to find other candidates in time, he added. Additional reporting by Stacy Hsu and staff writer 新聞來源：TAIPEI TIMES 
Chinese Nationalist Party （KMT） Legislator Chiang Wan-an speaks to reporters at the Legislative Yuan in Taipei yesterday.
Photo: Liao Chen-huei, Taipei Times 
Democratic Progressive Party Legislator Pasuya Yao, who has announced his plan to contest the Taipei mayoral election, expresses ""a sense of disappointment and loss"" to reporters in the Legislative Yuan yesterday after knowing that Chinese Nationalist Party Legislator Chiang Wan-an will not contest the election.
